input: Anne is big. Anne is blue. Anne is quiet. Anne is red. Anne is rough. Anne is round. Anne is young. Dave is red. Dave is rough. Dave is round. Dave is young. Fiona is round. Gary is big. Gary is not round. Round things are big. If Dave is young and Dave is red then Dave is rough. All blue, big things are young. If something is young and not big then it is blue. All round things are blue. Young things are rough. All rough, big things are red. Young, red things are quiet. If something is red and not rough then it is quiet. Question: Fiona is quiet.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Dave : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Gary : obj

constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Big Anne
axiom T2 : Blue Anne
axiom T3 : Quiet Anne
axiom T4 : Red Anne
axiom T5 : Rough Anne
axiom T6 : Round Anne
axiom T7 : Young Anne
axiom T8 : Red Dave
axiom T9 : Rough Dave
axiom T10 : Round Dave
axiom T11 : Young Dave
axiom T12 : Round Fiona
axiom T13 : Big Gary
axiom T14 : ¬ Round Gary

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Round x → Big x
axiom R2 : Young Dave ∧ Red Dave → Rough Dave
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Blue x ∧ Big x → Young x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Young x ∧ ¬ Big x → Blue x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Round x → Blue x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Rough x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Rough x ∧ Big x → Red x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Young x ∧ Red x → Quiet x
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ ¬ Rough x → Quiet x

theorem fiona_is_quiet : Quiet Fiona :=
begin
  apply R8,
  split,
  apply R3,
  split,
  apply R5,
  exact T12,
  apply R1,
  exact T12,
  apply R7,
  split,
  apply R6,
  apply R3,
  split,
  apply R5,
  exact T12,
  apply R1,
  exact T12,
end

-- The answer is True
